reviews.text:
Great place to spend the day. Not as flashy or as well known as the Intrepid or Midway, but a different experience from both as you have access to a huge portion of the ship and most of it is preserved as it was in 1970. Talk to the docents and take the guided tours they offer, you won't regret it. They have a restoration section on the hangar deck and as of this writing, they are restoring an F-8 and an AH-1. 

The ship is in need of some TLC and their aircraft collection is small compared to the other two museums I mentioned, but the staff is clearly dedicated and it was neat to see the ship in such an unvarnished state. I wouldn't hesitate to donate to the Hornet as I'm certain every dollar helps.

Great place for adults and kids of all ages. You can have a tour guide or explore on your own. Lots of history to see and learn about. There is snacks/food area kinda pricey for what is offered. There is a cover charge, but affordable, well worth it. Handicap accessible for disabled. Plenty of parking space.

They have so much information on aircraft, military, boats, and more. It is so much fun to walk around and have the history they give you seep into your mind. It is nice to know more information on the past. Their service is amazing and it is a fun place to go on a field trip.

Excellent museum!! There are interesting displays everywhere, from the lower deck with the kitchen, dormitories and hospital, the hangar deck with many planes as well as an Apollo program display. And the flight deck with helicopters and planes! Make sure you sign up for the engine tour and the bridge tour
Had a wonderful time combining the museum with a carrier.con event. Great history and knowledgeable doscents. Excellent costumes. An all-around perfect day. I would definitely go again.
Best Mexican food around. Love it.  Everything is amazing. Well worth your visit!
Great family owned business. We've been frequenting since day one, and our kids grew up on Calafia's food. Best Tacos in town, and the tamales and burritos are hard to beat.
Worst #$*#@!!?* Mexican food ever.. only thing good is the dark green Chile they have.. I'll never eat there again.

Definitely generous portions so either come starving or share a plate. Chips and salsa bar is cute and nice variety of salsas. Avoid the Chiles Rellenos though.. they're just soggy, wet, and have cheese and salsa tossed on top. decent tacos.
Great convenient Mexican food with self-serve sauces and plenty of chips
Love this place! Felt like I was in a movie set! Amazing food too and great prices & service. Fantastic coffee. Note - arrive early on weekends. By 9:30am there was a long line outside.

We adored this old diner that hops with activity.  The staff is fantastic - fast and efficient, a well-oiled professional diner machine.  
The menu is large - everyone will find something they want for every meal.  The specialty is breakfast, obviously waffles are heavy on the menu and live up to the diner hype.  You will pay a little extra for fresh fruit - but I think it's a nice option.  They list the fruits available that day on a sign at the front door.
Ole's has great sweet breakfasts - I loved the French Toast especially and there were a lot of orders of it going out.  But they also have plenty of savoury food - breakfast meats, eggs.
If you are a diner fan, Ole's is definitely worth a stop!  If you're not into diners, you will still find a consistent meal.

Had a great brunch at Ole’s today. Thank you Olga for the great service. I had chicken and waffles. It’s not actually on the menu here, but just ask for it if you want it. Pick any 2 pieces of chicken and they’ll cook it up to order. Super juicy and crispy, perfect with the waffle and warm maple syrup. 
HIGHLY RECOMMENDED 🌟

Perhaps the best pancakes that I have ever had.  They were light and fluffy and positively soaked up the butter and syrup.

The place always seems busy, but seats open quickly.  They have tables, booths, and a counter, and done of the friendliest and most efficient service I have had in a while.

Do yourself a favor and check this place out for yourself.

Family owned, breakfast counter/diner segment.  Walk into a cozy and bustling diner.  50's music playing and 80's sports memorabilia on the walls.  Great ingredients used in their standard breakfast menu.  The hickory smoked bacon flavor comes through in the ultimate omelette.  Hash browns were properly crispy on request.  Great service.  Prices par.  Portions a little more than par.  No reservations.  Typically a line, however they turn over tables very quickly.
I last visited several years ago and had not been at all impressed. At a recent visit, however, I was pleasantly surprised by how good the food was. I shall return.
Super solid taqueria. Taquitos are fresh, quality and delicious wrapped in flour tortillas. Tamales so good, whole beans seasoned to perfection. Def go back, nice change.
My favorite place to eat dinner with family before we go to the theater next door.  Their combination plates are huge, and really tasty.  A must-visit on movie nights.
Great food for a great price. Yummy salsa bar and friendly people.

Stopped in with the family for a quick bite before a movie and was pleasantly surprised. Food is just fine and reasonable priced, and also came out quick. The carnitas tacos were a tad oily and the onions were cooked (?) but the tacos were overall good. Kids were happy with their bean and cheese burritos. Chips were good and the salsas decent. We will be back when we need another quick bite.

When I go somewhere to eat I must feel welcomed, comfortable in a clean environment with good food. Not only dose Yojimbo have that but the nicest host and staff. I appreciate their service. Thank you!
The curry chicken is on point, great flavors.  My daughters love the cartoons playing on the TVs and obviously the food.
My family and I have been going here since the beginning and we love it now as much as we did The first time.  The sushi is fresh and delicious and portions are huge.  Love love this place
Loved the service and the food. I will absolutely come here again. Good amount of options for vegetarians.
Food is great and portions are large so expect to leave full! The art and ambiance are fantastic and the owner is genuinely nice.
Food great and staff attentive. Dining area a bit on the cozy side but then I did come with a large office party so we took up 2/3s of the tables. Downside is parking can be scarce in the area.

Delicious food with wonderful service and an attentive owner. Thank you for the generous and unasked for comp when my clumsy braced / broken wrists spilled my Remy. The chicken with fresh pear and sherry bechamel was amazing and delicious beyond expectations, delicious to the last bite! The wonderful service for our party of 6 was perfect. You have a lovely European ambiance I look forward to visiting again. Definitely 5 stars. 

Oh, and by the way, bring your own wine with an easy corkage fee, but the cocktails are immaculate.

This place is absolutely amazing! The staff is friendly and remembers me enough to always know my drink orders and that I want a steak!  This is by far the best restaurant in alameda in my opinion.  I love the staff, I love the drinks and I love the food.  If you haven't been here, you have to come our you are beyond missing out!

I've been going to this place for pretty close to 20 years with work friends. It's still our regular spot for getting together for lunch.  Their "house salad" itself is a true delight.  Also, I'm vegetarian and never struggled to have a delicious meal here.  Thanks so much!

We've been going here for over 20 years. It's an excellent option for a nice dinner on a special occasion or date night on the island. I love their house salad, the roasted garlic appetizer and you can't go wrong with the ravioli

I love this place with all my heart and soul. The food is always amazing as well as the employees. There is only one problem and it is that my order is always wrong. Call or order in person I am always missing something/given one order wrong, given less of what I've ordered, or getting extremely spicy food when I asked for it not to be spicy. I've spent close to or over $1,000 here and I've given up on believing my order is correct, but the food is too good not to come back. If I have to check my food visually and taste test it every time I'll gladly do it, I just wish I didn't have to.

The food and staff are great and friendly. Whenever I come here with my partner we tend to get a party platter, you get a little bit of a lot of things and it always fills us up. It's great if you are looking for a variety of items but don't want to order too much.

We were invited by our friend to have dinner. Food was horrible. Waiters they don't know what they were serving. They need more crew. They even missed the order. we ordered lamb curry, Thali, chicken tikka masala.
I will not recommend ruin our trip all the way from Santa Rosa.

this is my current favourite Indian restaurant. the dinner menu has a good selection, and the food is great. they also have a wider array of naan-like options than any other place i have tried. the parking lot is cramped and can be difficult to navigate.
The food is fresh and plentiful. The restaurant is easy to get to. The food is good.

I've been here over 10 years ago and recently. The service and food quality is still top notch. Large portions so be careful not to over order. I recently had their Mole enchilada. My first time eating Mole sauce. I thought it was delicious

Their Salsa and chips are amazing. We were promptly served our drinks with them upon sitting down at our table. They use corn tortillas for their street tacos which is way different from what I'm used to being served on flour tortillas.

My only gripe would be the prices. I live in Sacramento where even the best taco spots only charge $1.75 for street tacos. Here it is $2.99!

Chips and salsa are by far the best here! The waiters are usually friendly and check on you regularly. The food is tasty. It is great for drinks and the atmosphere is very lively. Loud salsa music, lots of people, it's fun.

Well first off, their salsa was amazing, even at 10pm on a Wednesday. That's all you really need to know. Great service, excellent food, strong margaritas. Real food. Decent prices. A+, this is no doubt the best Mexican restaurant in all of Alameda.
We had lunch there on a Sunday. They were very busy but no waiting for a table. Service friendly and quick. The food is very good. My father liked the shrimp cocktail.

Great food, decent beer, very cool atmosphere. Place is pretty pricey, especially for their beers. They sell 1 liter pints and 2 liter boots, but it's the same price per oz. As their smaller selections, so a boot can easily cost you over $30

Wonderful place to drop in for high quality music, food and drink.  Easy place to drop in and talk to friendly locals if you're alone, and very accommodating if you want to reserve a table to meet, dine and dance with a large group of friends.  The food is always good, the music never disappoints.  So gotta give 'em 5 stars.

We had a wonderful experience at Speisekammer. My husband took me there for my birthday. The food was delicious,  the cocktail I ordered was great and the service was good too. I ordered the lamb shank,  which came with some really tasty charred brussel sprouts. My husband also enjoyed the cabbage rolls he ordered. What a find!

I wish I would have written a detailed review on this place immediately, because I would have been able to describe it better. The food was better than expected, and I went in with good expectations. It took a about 10-15 minutes to get my food, which is a good thing in my opinion--it was definitely freshly cooked. Unfortunately, I was working at the time and couldn't enjoy a beer to go with my meal. The price was good, and they give fair portions. Check this place out! I can't wait to make an excuse to go back to Alameda just to go here again.

So this was a pretty cool and funky place. It was a nice afternoon in Alameda, so we sat outside with our dog. The pretzel and cheese was outstanding, and the currywurst was decent. Drinks were good, but a little slow. Maybe our server was baked

Incredible sushi spot- 5 stars doesn’t do this place justice. It’s probably the best sushi I’ve ever had including on trips to Japan, and all around the world. This place is incredible. If you want the classic experience, this is the place.
This place is amazing. From the B-dama and Delage family. I out this up there with maruya and kenzo
Experience places the food at its center, as it should be.  Great time!
Excellent sushi, well presented. Place is quite cold (I don't mean temperature) and unadorned, not warm or cozy in the least.

I've never gone to a place like this before, and it was definitely an amazing and unique experience. Each bite of food is different and full of flavor, and the atmosphere is also great. Sorry for taking photos!
